# Generate a Tracker From Scratch
# AI builds an entire SharePoint list from a plain English description — columns, sample data, and views.

[var: SITE = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

[section: setup]

Verify the site does NOT have a list called "Product Launch Tracker." If one
exists from a previous run, delete it before proceeding.

[navigate: ${SITE}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

Confirm the chat pane is fresh and the site home page is visible.

[pause]

[section: demo]

[navigate: ${SITE}]

Let's say your team just kicked off a product launch and you need a way to
track everything. Normally you'd spend 20 minutes creating a list, adding
columns, choosing column types, entering sample data. Instead, let's just
describe what we need.

[pause]

[open-chat]

[prompt: Create a list called "Product Launch Tracker" for managing a cross-functional product launch. I need to track tasks across Engineering, Marketing, Sales, and Support teams. Include columns for the task, the owner, the team, a due date, status, and any blockers. Add 12 sample rows with realistic tasks that cover all four teams across a 6-week launch timeline.]

[wait]

Copilot created the entire list — columns, column types, and 12 rows of
realistic sample data. Notice it chose the right types automatically: Choice
columns for Team and Status, Date for Due Date, text for Blockers. Point out
the sample tasks — API documentation, press releases, CRM updates, knowledge
base articles. These are plausible, not filler.

[pause]

Now let's add a useful view on top of it.

[prompt: Create a view called "This Week" that shows only tasks due in the next 7 days, grouped by Team, sorted by Due Date.]

[wait]

A filtered view in seconds. The team can now see exactly what's due this week,
grouped by department. No manual view configuration needed.

[pause]

One more — let's use AI to actually manage the tracker.

[prompt: Which tasks are blocked, and what would you suggest to unblock them?]

[wait]

Copilot read the Blockers column and provided actionable suggestions. From
zero to a fully functional project tracker with smart views and AI-powered
status checks — in about 90 seconds.

[pause]

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/11-generate-tracker-final.png]

[section: reset]

Delete the "Product Launch Tracker" list to restore the site.

[navigate: ${SITE}_layouts/15/viewlsts.aspx]

[confirm: Delete the "Product Launch Tracker" list from Site Contents]

[new-chat]
